      "title": "Isothermal Elastohydrodynamic Lubrication of Point Contacts: Part III-Fully Flooded Results",
      "abstract": "Abstract The theory developed by the authors in an earlier publication was used to investigate the influ- ence of the ellipticity parameter and the dimensionless speed U, load W, and material G pa- rameters on minimum film thickness. The ellipticity parameter k was varied from l (a ball- on-plate configuration) to 8 (a configuration approaching a line contact). speed parameter was varied over a range of nearly two orders of magnitude. And the dimen- sionless load parameter was varied over a range of one order of magnitude. Conditions cor- responding to the use of solid materials of bronze, steel, and silicon nitride and lubricants of paraffinic and naphthenic mineral oils were considered in obtaining the exponent on the dimen- sionless material param5ter. Thirty-four different cases were used in obtaining the minimum- film-thickness formula Hmin = 3.63 U'. 68Go' 49W-0* 073 (1 - e -\" 68k). A simplified expression for ellipticity parameter k = 1.03 (R /Rx)"
